   "source": [
    "# Vuvuzela?\n",
    "\n",
    "Vuvuzela? , Vuvuzela(). , , , . \n",
    "\n",
    "![image.png](attachment:image.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "Vuvuzela? , .\n",
    "\n",
    ">Vuvuzela cancellation with spectral subtraction technique. Based on the spectrum of the\n",
    "vuvuzela only sound, this denoising technique simply computes an\n",
    "antenuation map in the time-frequency domain. Then, the audio signal is\n",
    "obtained by computing the inverse STFT. See [1] or [2] for\n",
    "more detail about the algorithm.\n",
    "\n",
    "References:\n",
    "\n",
    "[1] Steven F. Boll, \"Suppression of Acoustic Noise in Speech Using Spectral\n",
    "Subtraction\", IEEE Transactions on Signal Processing, 27(2),pp 113-120,\n",
    "1979\n",
    "\n",
    "[2] Y. Ephraim and D. Malah, ?Speech enhancement using a minimum mean square error \n",
    " short-time spectral amplitude estimator,? IEEE. Transactions in Acoust., Speech, Signal\n",
    " Process., vol. 32, no. 6, pp. 1109?1121, Dec. 1984.\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: The file: Vuvuzela.wav must be located in the folder of this script file.\n",
    "One can note that this time-frequency based technique creates a \"musical\n",
    "noise\".\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "Programmed by V. Choqueuse (contact: vincent.choqueuse@gmail.com)\n",
    "\n",
    "Python version is programmed by L. Yu (Contact: ly.wd@whu.edu.cn)\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },

    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import numpy.matlib\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from scipy.io import wavfile\n",
    "import matplotlib.cm as cm\n",
    "from scipy import signal\n",
    "from scipy.fftpack import fft,ifft\n",
    "import sounddevice as sd\n",
    "\n",
    "print('--- Vuvuzela Cancelation Program ---\\n\\n');\n",
    "\n",
    "# load vuvuzela sound example\n",
    "print('-> Step 1/5: Load vuvuzela.wav:')\n",
    "Fe, y = wavfile.read('Vuvuzela.wav')\n",
    "x     = y[100000:].astype('float')\n",
    "Nx    = x.size\n",
    "print(' OK\\n')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(np.arange(0,len(x))/Fe,x)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Time (s)')\n",
    "plt.title('Original Signal with Vuvuzela')"
   ]

   "source": [
    "## \n",
    "(STFT)[](https://baike.baidu.com/item/%E9%9D%9E%E5%B9%B3%E7%A8%B3%E4%BF%A1%E5%8F%B7).\n",
    "\n",
    "![image.png](attachment:image.png)\n",
    "\n",
    ", $M$$g[n]$, . ,:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "X_{m}(f)=\\sum_{n=-\\infty}^{\\infty} x(n) g(n-m R) e^{-j 2 \\pi f n}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "$R$, $R=M-L$. $L$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "# %STFT parameters\n",
    "NFFT          =1024                               # DFT\n",
    "window_length =(np.round(0.031*Fe)).astype('int') # \n",
    "window        = signal.hamming(window_length)     # \n",
    "overlap       = np.floor(0.45*window_length)      # \n",
    "#construct spectrogram \n",
    "F, T, S       = signal.spectrogram(x+1j*1e-16,Fe, window=window,noverlap=window_length-overlap,nfft=NFFT) \n",
    "# put a short imaginary part to obtain two-sided spectrogram\n",
    "Nf,Nw         = S.shape\n",
    "\n",
    "t_epsilon = 1e-2\n",
    "S_one_sided=np.abs(S[:np.array(len(F)/2).astype('int'),...])\n",
    "S_one_sided[S_one_sided<t_epsilon]=t_epsilon\n",
    "plt.pcolormesh(T,F[:np.array(len(F)/2).astype('int')],np.log(S_one_sided),cmap=plt.cm.hot)\n",
    "plt.title('Spectrogram: speech only');\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Time (s)');\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frequency (Hz)');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "-> Step 2/5: Extract noise spectrum -\n",
      "OK\n",
      "\n",
      "(1024, 1935)\n"
     ]

    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# %----------------------------%\n",
    "# %        noisy spectrum      %\n",
    "# %          extraction        %\n",
    "# %----------------------------%\n",
    "# Signal parameters\n",
    "t_min       = 0.4    #interval for learning the noise\n",
    "t_max       = 1.00   #spectrum (in second)\n",
    "print('-> Step 2/5: Extract noise spectrum -');\n",
    "absS_vuvuzela = np.abs(S[...,(np.double(T>t_min) + np.double(T<t_max))>=2])**2\n",
    "vuvuzela_spectrum = np.mean(absS_vuvuzela,axis=1)\n",
    "plt.plot(vuvuzela_spectrum)\n",
    "vuvuzela_specgram = np.transpose(np.matlib.repmat(vuvuzela_spectrum,Nw,1))\n",
    "print('OK\\n')\n",
    "print(vuvuzela_specgram.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "-> Step 3/5: Estimate SNR -\n",
      " OK\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# %---------------------------%\n",
    "# %       Estimate SNR        %\n",
    "# %---------------------------%\n",
    "\n",
    "print('-> Step 3/5: Estimate SNR -');\n",
    "absS=np.abs(S)**2\n",
    "SNR_est = absS/vuvuzela_specgram - 1\n",
    "SNR_est[SNR_est<0] = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "# \n",
    "apriori_SNR = 1  # select 0 for aposteriori SNR estimation and 1 for apriori (see [2])\n",
    "alpha       = 0.05      # only used if apriori_SNR=1\n",
    "if apriori_SNR==1:\n",
    "    SNR_est=signal.lfilter([1-alpha],[1,-alpha],SNR_est)  #a priori SNR: see [2]\n",
    "print(' OK\\n');\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# \n",
    "t_epsilon = 1e-2\n",
    "S_one_sided=np.abs(SNR_est[:np.array(len(F)/2).astype('int'),...])\n",
    "S_one_sided[S_one_sided<t_epsilon]=t_epsilon\n",
    "plt.pcolormesh(T,F[:np.array(len(F)/2).astype('int')],np.log(S_one_sided),cmap=plt.cm.hot)\n",
    "plt.title('Spectrogram: Noise');\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Time (s)');\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frequency (Hz)');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## \n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "A_m(f) = \\left(1- \\frac{\\lambda}{\\mbox{SNR}_m(f)^{\\beta_1}}\\right)^{\\beta_2}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "w_m(f) = \n",
    "\\begin{cases}\n",
    " A_m(f) & \\mbox{ if } A_m(f) \\geq 0 \\\\\n",
    " 0 & \\mbox{else}\n",
    "\\end{cases}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\hat{X}_m(f) = A_m(f)\\cdot X_m(f)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "> : SNR,(1), ; , SNR, (0), ."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "-> Step 4/5: Compute TF attenuation map -\n",
      " OK\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# %---------------------------%\n",
    "# %  Compute attenuation map  %\n",
    "# %---------------------------%\n",
    "print('-> Step 4/5: Compute TF attenuation map -');\n",
    "beta1       = 0.5\n",
    "beta2       = 1\n",
    "lam         = 3\n",
    "an_lk = (1-lam*((1/(SNR_est+1))**beta1))**beta2\n",
    "an_lk[an_lk<0] = 0\n",
    "STFT=an_lk*S\n",
    "print(' OK\\n')\n",
    "\n",
    "# \n",
    "t_epsilon = 1e-2\n",
    "plt.subplot(311)\n",
    "S_one_sided=np.abs(S[:np.array(len(F)/2).astype('int'),...])\n",
    "S_one_sided[S_one_sided<t_epsilon]=t_epsilon\n",
    "plt.pcolormesh(T,F[:np.array(len(F)/2).astype('int')],np.log(S_one_sided),cmap=plt.cm.hot)\n",
    "plt.title('Spectrogram: Original Speech');\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Time (s)');\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frequency (Hz)');\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(312)\n",
    "S_one_sided=np.abs(an_lk[:np.array(len(F)/2).astype('int'),...])\n",
    "S_one_sided[S_one_sided<t_epsilon]=t_epsilon\n",
    "plt.pcolormesh(T,F[:np.array(len(F)/2).astype('int')],np.log(S_one_sided),cmap=plt.cm.hot)\n",
    "plt.title('Spectrogram: Weights');\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Time (s)');\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frequency (Hz)');\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(313)\n",
    "S_one_sided=np.abs(STFT[:np.array(len(F)/2).astype('int'),...])\n",
    "S_one_sided[S_one_sided<t_epsilon]=t_epsilon\n",
    "plt.pcolormesh(T,F[:np.array(len(F)/2).astype('int')],np.log(S_one_sided),cmap=plt.cm.hot)\n",
    "plt.title('Spectrogram: Speech after denoising');\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Time (s)');\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frequency (Hz)');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {
    "image.png": {
     "image/png": ""
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## \n",
    "IFFT, :\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{aligned}_{x(n)} &=\\int_{-1 / 2}^{1 / 2} \\sum_{m=-\\infty}^{\\infty} X_{m}(f) e^{j 2 \\pi f n} d f \\\\ &=\\sum_{m=-\\infty}^{\\infty} \\int_{-1 / 2}^{1 / 2} X_{m}(f) e^{j 2 \\pi f n} d f \\\\ &=\\sum_{m=-\\infty}^{\\infty} x_{m}(n) \\end{aligned}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "![image.png](attachment:image.png)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "-> Step 5/5: Compute Inverse STFT:\n",
      " OK\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# %--------------------------%\n",
    "# %   Compute Inverse STFT   %\n",
    "# %--------------------------%\n",
    "\n",
    "print('-> Step 5/5: Compute Inverse STFT:')\n",
    "ind=np.mod(np.arange(0,window_length),Nf)\n",
    "output_signal=np.zeros([np.int((Nw)*overlap+window_length),])\n",
    "\n",
    "for indice in range(Nw): #Overlapp add technique\n",
    "#     print(indice)\n",
    "    left_index=((indice)*overlap) \n",
    "    index=(left_index+np.arange(0,window_length)).astype('int64')\n",
    "    temp_ifft=np.real(ifft(STFT[...,indice],NFFT))\n",
    "    output_signal[index]= output_signal[index]+temp_ifft[ind]*window\n",
    "print(' OK\\n')"
   ]
  },
